sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller Manager<br/>(Job Framework Controllers)
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Scheduler
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>OpenShift Monitoring

    Note over User,Scheduler: Flow 1: Job Admission via Webhook

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create job/pytorchjob<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token / Client Cert
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-*<br/>HTTPS/443→9443, API server client cert
    Webhook->>Webhook: Suspend job, inject queue label
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated job (suspended=true)
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job created (suspended)

    Note over Controller,Scheduler: Flow 2: Workload Scheduling

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch for suspended jobs<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Workload CR<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Read Workloads, ClusterQueues<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Evaluate quotas, fair sharing,<br/>priorities, resource flavors
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Update Workload status (admit)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Unsuspend Job / update annotations<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Job pods start running

    Note over K8sAPI,Webhook: Flow 3: Validation Webhook

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create clusterqueue<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-*<br/>HTTPS/443→9443, API server client cert
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate CR spec
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Allowed / Denied
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR created / rejected

    Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 4: Metrics Scraping

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>HTTPS/8443, Bearer Token
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics<br/>(queue depths, admission latency, etc.)
